    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Trim, then roughly chop your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>and then top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> in half lengthways then slice diagonally into half-moons</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into small, bite-sized pieces, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger </strong>and<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken thighs </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>cornflour </strong>and and give everything a good mix up until the chicken is fully coated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and your <strong>soy sauce </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until the chicken has started to brown and crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, add the <strong>sliced carrot</strong>,<strong> chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>spring onion</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 2-3 min until softened</p><p>Once the carrot and pepper have softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong> and your <strong>cashew nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>water </strong>to the pan, give everything a good mix up and cook for 2-3 min until thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Add another splash of water if it's looking a little thick!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, stir through your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped spring onion </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style cashew chicken thigh</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-cashew-chicken-thigh-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese-style cashew chicken thigh</strong> over the<strong> cooked cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
